<paragraph blockId="68.[189,1399,1892,2025]" lastBlockId="70.[188,1399,265,432]" lastPageId="70" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y." box="[189,498,1892,1918]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="313 - 321" refId="ref48523" refString="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y. 1998. New species and new records of hover-flies of the genus Cheilosia Mg. from China (Diptera: Syrphidae). Zoosystematica Rossica 7: 313 - 321." type="journal article" year="1998">Barkalov &amp; Cheng (1998)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="1998" box="[626,819,1892,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucida">
<emphasis box="[626,819,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Cheilosia lucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the male sex, and the taxon was placed in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov, 2002" authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2002" box="[391,740,1927,1953]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Convocheila">
<emphasis box="[391,543,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Convocheila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov A. V." box="[551,740,1927,1953]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="218 - 234" refId="ref48378" refString="Barkalov A. V. 2002. A subgeneric classification of the genus Cheilosia Meigen, 1822 (Diptera, Syrphidae). Entomologicheskoe obozrenie 81: 218 - 234. [In Russian.]" type="journal article" year="2002">Barkalov, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y." box="[753,1073,1927,1953]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="267 - 416" refId="ref48566" refString="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y. 2004. Revision of the genus Cheilosia Meigen, 1822 (Diptera: Syrphidae) of China. Contributions on Entomology International 5: 267 - 416." type="journal article" year="2004">Barkalov &amp; Cheng (2004)</bibRefCitation>
described the female. The structure of the distiphallus (apical sclerite of the aedeagus) and the shapes of the strongly asymmetric superior lobes and surstylus are very different from other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2002" box="[959,1105,1998,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Convocheila">
<emphasis box="[959,1105,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Convocheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov A. V." box="[1164,1394,1998,2024]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="218 - 234" refId="ref48378" refString="Barkalov A. V. 2002. A subgeneric classification of the genus Cheilosia Meigen, 1822 (Diptera, Syrphidae). Entomologicheskoe obozrenie 81: 218 - 234. [In Russian.]" type="journal article" year="2002">Barkalov 2002: 230</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y." box="[189,535,265,292]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="267 - 416" refId="ref48566" refString="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y. 2004. Revision of the genus Cheilosia Meigen, 1822 (Diptera: Syrphidae) of China. Contributions on Entomology International 5: 267 - 416." type="journal article" year="2004">Barkalov &amp; Cheng 2004: 395</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Radenkovic S. &amp; Likov L. &amp; Stahls G. &amp; Rojo S. &amp; Perez-Banon C. &amp; Smit J. &amp; Petanidou T. &amp; van Steenis W. &amp; Vujic A." box="[546,821,265,291]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="103 - 124" refId="ref49888" refString="Radenkovic S., Likov L., Stahls G., Rojo S., Perez-Banon C., Smit J., Petanidou T., van Steenis W. &amp; Vujic A. 2020. Three new hoverfly species from Greece (Diptera: Syrphidae). Zootaxa 4830 (1): 103 - 124. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4830.1.4" type="journal article" year="2020">
Radenkovic 
<emphasis box="[692,749,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="1998" box="[979,1171,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucida">
<emphasis box="[979,1171,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Cheilosia lucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a characteristic lustrous green shine (reflection) of the thorax and strong black bristles on scutellum margin, characteristics not shared by other members of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2002" box="[742,889,335,361]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Convocheila">
<emphasis box="[742,889,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Convocheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, the subgeneric classification of this species requires further study. From all species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[775,887,370,396]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[775,887,370,396]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Cheilosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="1998" box="[902,1009,370,397]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucida">
<emphasis box="[902,1009,370,397]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">C. lucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the combination of the mentioned characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
